		<div class="comment-text">
			<p>Jonathan M &#8211; I made this dish 3/1/11.  I think there was an article in Saveur mag about it.  I roasted bones to make a stock.  Placed raw slices of sirloin on top of blanched noodles, poured broth over the whole thing in large bowls.  I have a picture of it.  Thought it was called Pho Bac or some such.  Pronounced Feu as in the French &#8220;fire&#8221;.  A great meal.  Even made a separate stock and bowl for a vegetarian.</p>

